==Chinese==

===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{liushu|i}} – An inverted {{l|zh|曰}} ("to speak"), hence [[亼]] with a horizontal stroke at the bottom, so the inverted mouth means "not to speak".

Another theory suggests that it depicts something in the mouth. Maybe the original form of {{och-l|噤}} or {{och-l|吟}}. If so, the derivative {{och-l|含}} refers to the original word.

